flowRoot.flowPara: I started getting into photography around 13, and learned a lot by practicing on my old point and shoot. It wasn't until a few years later that I splurged on a real DSLR for better pictures, but by then I had forgotten quite a bit. My weapon of choice is a Nikon D5300 with a 18-55mm kit lens.

I like the zoom lenses for a lot of wildlife photography, but nothing beats a wide angle landscape in my opinion. While I'm not going to toss up all my work on this site (bandwith and what not), I'll post my favorites in hopes that people enjoy them!
